tip.text: Nice donburi. Not the best grade sashimi, but delicious nonetheless.
Amazing bouncy, tasty fish balls. Try the soup noodle or dry with chilli. Delicious!

formattedAddress: Food Opera, #B4-04B, ION Orchard (2 Orchard Turn)

tip.text: Now a nice art museum! Definitely check out the artist Oba's work - very impressive.

venue.name: Former Hokkaido Government Office (北海道庁 赤れんが庁舎)

tip.text: Wander around. Lots of pokemon to catch. Fountain gets turned on at night. There's a nice slide to try too!
Beautiful and peaceful. Lots to see and wander around. Includes an Anui museum (watch out, has old footage of traditional bear sacrifice ceremony), and a smaller taxidermy museum.

venue.name: Botanic Garden Hokkaido University (北海道大学 植物園)

tip.text: Amazing. Try one. You won't regret it. Buttery shortcrust pastry with a subtle cheese flavour filling.

formattedAddress: 北区北6条西3 (JR札幌駅 サツエキ イート内)
location.crossStreet: JR札幌駅 サツエキ イート内

tip.text: Delicious miso base ramen that will warm you up on a cold night. Butter corn uses real corn! Has pork bits, cabbage, shoots, bamboo. Very tasty broth!

formattedAddress: 中央区南6条西3丁目 (睦ビル1F)

tip.text: Room smells smoky and older building but wow it's worth it for the buffet breakfast. Huge range, delicious food and they have cake at breakfast!!!

venue.name: Century Royal Hotel (センチュリーロイヤルホテル)
Cupnoodles Museum (カップヌードルミュージアム)
Cupnoodles Museum (カップヌードルミュージアム)
Cupnoodles Museum (カップヌードルミュージアム)
Cupnoodles Museum (カップヌードルミュージアム)
Cupnoodles Museum (カップヌードルミュージアム)
Cupnoodles Museum (カップヌードルミュージアム)
Cupnoodles Museum (カップヌードルミュージアム)

tip.text: A good fun day that's suitable for every age. Try making your own noodles (take home pack) or creating your own cup noodle to take home. Try different countries' noodle dishes and learn about momofuku

venue.name: Cupnoodles Museum (カップヌードルミュージアム)

tip.text: Try as much food as you can! There's also a lot of fish related goods - knives, crockery, dried fish, snacks...
My favourite place in the world. 15 storeys of stationary goodness, and tax free available! They have a whole floor dedicated to ink pens.
Nice sushi and sashimi but nothing to rave about, you can probably get just as good for cheaper around the market. The wait isn't very long though which is good.

venue.name: Sushizanmai (すしざんまい 本店)

tip.text: Both the chicken and sardine style soba are different but incredible in their own ways. If you can try both, i'd recommend it, but if you only have one shot - chicken all the way.
Takoyaki that you can dress yourself with as much or as little condiment as you want. Nice and creamy and served immediately. Love it
Chewy Ox tongue. Very tasty sets. Try the tomato stew! The broth is delicious. No line at 22:00.

formattedAddress: 北区北6条西2丁目1-7 (パセオ ウエスト B1F)
location.crossStreet: パセオ ウエスト B1F

venue.name: 牛たん炭焼 利久 パセオ店

tip.text: Tsukiji market on the main outer street with all the food facing the road. Managed to snag the last bowl, get here before 13:00 or risk missing out. Fantastic flavour, generous serve. Love it.
Absolutely incredible donburi. Wow. Beautiful fresh fish, and tasty! Make sure you ask for the amazing broth when you're finished to enjoy with extra rice. Worth the wait.

Nice shopping strip leading up to the temple, you can dress up in traditional yukata for nice photos. Temple itself is under construction so you couldn't see inside but still a nice wander in the area
Their banana and rum milkshake was to die for! But expensive. Quite a fancier quieter bar with prices to match. Nice service and good English from the staff!

location.address: 銀座 7-5-4 ラヴィアーレ銀座ビル 7F
formattedAddress: 銀座 7-5-4 ラヴィアーレ銀座ビル 7F

tip.text: Lots of food to try so skip lunch! Watch out for more expensive prices on items and gifts as its a popular tourist spot. Love this market - find the spicy powder and thank me later!

formattedAddress: 中京区西大文字町609 (富小路通四条上ル)

tip.text: My favourite temple in Kyoto, maybe even Japan. Currently undergoing restoration so the beautiful photo worthy shot is a bit marred, still a lovely walk with scenery, temples and shopping strip.
Quite a short street with older style shops, a lot of habidasheries. Wouldn't go out of my way to visit, more just if you're in the area. There's a shop that sells fried foods - great for a snack!

venue.name: Yanaka Ginza Shotengai (谷中銀座商店街)

tip.text: Ueno-San's diamond ice is pretty cool to watch. The bar tenders are multicultural and staff speak excellent English. The cocktails don't disappoint, give them flavours and they will work their magic!

formattedAddress: 銀座5-4-15 (エフローレギンザ5ビル B1F)
location.crossStreet: エフローレギンザ5ビル B1F

tip.text: Definitely get the lobster roll. I preferred shrimp over crab. It's pricy and there will be a queue. But surprisingly fresh and quite tasty given the lobster is from Maine.
Peaceful and beautiful. Take some time out and walk through these gardens and the shrine area. You won't regret it.
It's true, pan fried is better. Thin skinned succulent meat filling. Try the cucumber and the bean sprouts with meat sauce. Worth the queue.
Amazing tasty broth with noodles that are firm and great to absorb the full flavour of the broth. The machine where you order is in japanese but the servers will assist. Try the "lot" and "spicy".

formattedAddress: 丸の内1-9-1 (東京駅一番街 B1F 東京ラーメンストリート)
location.crossStreet: 東京駅一番街 B1F 東京ラーメンストリート

tip.text: fat cow donburri is better than then foie gras donburri. Aim for each mouthful to contain a cube of Wagyu and foie gras, otherwise the rice and meat is quite plain - the taste is in the foie gras.
I preferred the Momofuku ramen to the spicy which was a tad spicy and the broth not as tasty. The shrimp Bao is the best Bao I've tasted ever. Better than the pork belly. Do it.
The service is friendly but the food isn't anything spectacular. Had the Okame Soba (not enough meat) and Oyako Don (not bad). The tempura was nice and fresh.
FKN amazing icecream. I was pleasantly surprised. Rice and the maple pecan. Epic. Do yourself a favour and get the bigger cup size.

formattedAddress: 151 W 34th St Fl 6 (Macy's Herald Sq., 35th and Broadway)

tip.text: Beautiful fresh fish. Omakase is around $150pp for 15 or so pieces. Perfect service and lovely atmosphere.
Spicy burger is mild but tender and juicy. A nice semi-sweet bun. The chick-fil-a sauce is nice. Like a mustard Mayo. Long lines but effective system.
Pho isn't bad. Good flavoured broth but noodles are thin rice vermicelli. The Bun Bo Hue also has a lot of flavour with a nice spicy hit and thicker udon-type rice noodles. Good smattering of meat.
Holy shit. Good ass burgers (smokeshack) and cheesy fries. The concrete frozen custard creations are great. Chocolate hit comes in the form of the Murray Hill Malt.

venue.name: Menya Sandaime Ramen 面屋三代目

formattedAddress: Cnr La Trobe and Swanston St.
location.address: Cnr La Trobe and Swanston St.

formattedAddress: 156 Gertrude St. (btwn Napier & Little George St)

tip.text: The Bloody George is much like the Mary but has a nice meaty flavour to it. Quite enjoyed it. Perfect spice.
Gelato that reminds me of Italy, creamy and interesting flavours. Quite enjoyable indeed. Different to Messina.
Camebert flavoured gelato is seriously the strangest taste I have ever encountered for ice-cream. Salty sweet with definite Camebert bits, I'm glad I tried it.
Lavender white choc, plum sorbet and kiwi banana sorbet were all delicious! Creamy fast-melting gelato. Small serve due to beautiful presentation but still worth going!
Best in Rome, really nice complex flavours like garden sage and raspberry and cheese almond fig. Really enjoyed it but more expensive than others.

formattedAddress: Via dei Coronari, 65 (Via di San Simone 70)

tip.text: Of course you have to visit this legendary structure. Don't be too disappointed in it's ruins, it's still a wonderous feat. Also, if you want the third level/underground tour, BOOK MONTHS IN ADVANCE!!

formattedAddress: Piazza del Colosseo (Via dei Fori Imperiali)

tip.text: Thick pizza is damn thick! But the bread is delicious and filling. The toppings aren't pulled on but delicious nonetheless! Give it a shot
£5 for pastas, don't be scared by the Asian noodles on the menu (Asian and Italian chef), nice quick meal. Friendly service. I enjoyed the bolognese best out of carbonara and zucchini shrimp.
Yummy snack food, lots to choose from; ask for the menu in your language. I recommend the Americain, the fish liver pate and the croquette!
Dat Bloody Mary. Best I've had in Europe - and I've been searching far and wide. A lovely spice combo. Food is great though small and not that filling. Great hot chocolate too.

formattedAddress: Arch 250 Paradise Row (Bethnal Green Road and Nant Street)
location.crossStreet: Bethnal Green Road and Nant Street

tip.text: Bloody amazing food, best meal in Cambridge. Their sauces (esp mushroom) are creamy and delicious. And dat butterscotch sticky toffee pud. Also yummy hot choc! Nice service too.
I am Asian. Amazing xiaolongbao. Really nice noodles and even the Taiwanese omelette. Bit weird you have to knock on the door though. Haha
Epic sloppy burgers; dead hippy better than red chilli. The milkshake is fkn fantastic, liking drinking a softserve, and even more so with bourbon. The chili fries and buffalo wings are fantastic.
Sweet burger br0. Great pattie, very nicely cooked with a BBQ feel to it. Chips are great and the alioli had a nice lemony tang to it (but is quite expensive)
Ice cream is naturally made. Strawberry is lovely and light and creamy. The St Clements is amazing, a tangy sorbet of orange and lemon. Cookie on it's own not great, hard to chew.
Great cookies. Chewy, with high quality chocolate. Charged by weight, roughly £1.40 per cookie. Nommy!
Dirty Eaton Mess is brill. Very yummy. Bloody Mary is a bit weird - too much lime?
Pork special burrito was great, meat not as tasty as the chicken but even the small size is super filling. Yum! I'd return.
Raspberry amazing. Really creamy icecream. Cherry a bit fake (v sweet) but still ok. Note: pic is half eaten.
My gosh. The lemon ripple raspberry cake is incredible. The red velvet is to be eaten, but I'm sure it will also be fantastic! Glad I visited here. Put it on your to-do list.
Super nice - of course. And the star dishes are there for a reason: meat fruit and tipsy cake, I would return again and again. The pork chop and bass were great as well!
Super nice to ride through

Had the chicken burrito, nice and cheesy with great fat chicken bits. What made it even better was the fact they saved it for us  (we were late for a tour) and reheated it when we returned 4hrs later.
